associated(pointer) tells whether a pointer is associated.
associated(pointer, target) tells whether it is associated with target.

after nullify:
associated(p) = F
associated(q) = F
associated(r) = F

after p => a, q => a, r => x:
associated(p) = T
associated(q) = T
associated(r) = T

target tests:
associated(p, a) = T
associated(p, b) = F
associated(q, a) = T
associated(r, x) = T

pointer-to-pointer target tests:
associated(p, q) = T

after q => b:
associated(p, q) = F
associated(q, b) = T

after p => a(2:4):
p = 2 3 4
associated(p) = T
associated(p, a) = F
associated(p, a(2:4)) = T

after nullify(p):
associated(p) = F
